stylometry: A RISKSIM table allows you to see the varied possible outcomes of the RISKSIM spreadsheet. With this you can see how the risks and outcomes change when the inputs change (such as demand, pricing). A good example of this would be in a simulation model analyzing profits given demand and costs associated with a product. With the RISKSIM table, you can look at what happens to the profits when the inputs (demand or costs) are changed. After analyzing the table, you can identify which outcome poses the least risk.
